root.str: This scanner is designed for those who always want more. Hand-assembled and using military components, it provides better scanning and a fast charge rate making this Scanner the best tool to scan any existing sea creature.

Optimized for stealth and subterfuge, this armor merges ASE's nanoweave protection with Excavion's adaptive camouflage. Some recent models feature traces of unfamiliar circuitry, sparking speculation that the Crows have acquired-and perhaps are repurposing-tech that doesn't belong to the NC.

This armor can only be worn by NC Infiltrators.
Show your friends and foes how lucky (or unlucky) they are to have you around with this Leprechaun Horn!
Move aside - it is an emergency! Clear your way using the new EVL horn.

The Easter Egg Grenade, for when you want an egg-splosive presence on the battlefield!
Capable of heavily damaging infantry targets.

3 second fuse.

Available during the Easter Period.

Designed for those who endure the brunt of battle, this armor melds ASE's top-tier ballistic plating with Excavion's reinforced framework. Rumors suggest some suits have been field-tested against non-traditional weaponry-perhaps in anticipation of threats yet to be faced.

This armor can only be worn by NC Heavy Assault Troopers.

Perfect for Crows who need to strike fast, and, escape even faster. The jetpack is integrated with enhancements on ASE's Lateral Leap Accelerator, with improved aerodynamics incorporated into the aesthethics, and, optimal burst-thrust efficiency. These bespoke models have even been tested with unconventional energy resistance, hinting that the Legion's ambitions extend beyond traditional warfare.

This armor can only be worn by NC Light Assault Troopers.
Due to the scanner tools' popularity, all basic model components were redesigned from scratch to exceed its limitations. This approach positively affects scanning power and battery charge rate.

Essential for the Legion's tech-savvy operators, this armor integrates ASE's modular plating with Exavion's custom utility harness. Designed for quick access to tools, explosives, and ammunition, it's favored by Crows who prefer to keep their squad in fighting shape while staying one step ahead of enemy armor.

This armor integrates ASE's modular plating with Excavion's custom utility harness. A few engineers have been spotted modifying their suits with unfamiliar interface ports-suggesting the Crows are tinkering with something outside standard NC hardware.

This armor can only be worn by NC Engineers.

Combat medics in the Legion of the Crows don't just save lives; they adapt, experiment, and survive. While this armor is built for durability and mobility, a few units have been seen with unusual interface ports and concealed compartments-suggesting the Crows may be preparing for more than just emergency care.

This armor can only be worn by NC Combat Medics.
